@anchor{Function map-derangements}
@deffn {Function} {map-derangements} function sequence @&key start end copy
@findex map-derangements
Calls @code{function} with each derangement of the subsequence of @code{sequence} denoted
by the bounding index designators @code{start} and @code{end}. Derangement is a permutation
of the sequence where no element remains in place. @code{sequence} is not modified,
but individual derangements are @code{eq} to each other. Consequences are unspecified
if calling @code{function} modifies either the derangement or @code{sequence}.
@end deffn
